      "content": "it's just that the exhaustion isn't even physical anymore. it's like my soul is just... empty. i look at the empty house and i just feel like i've failed at the only thing i was actually meant to do. everything feels so heavy and hopeless. sometimes i just think i'd be better off if i could just sleep and never have to face this again.",
